WEBVTT

00:10.511 --> 00:11.887
♪ You could do it solo ♪

00:11.887 --> 00:13.931
♪ But then you'd be all by yourself ♪

00:13.931 --> 00:16.517
♪ Yo! So, it'd be more fun
To share this one ♪

00:16.517 --> 00:17.935
♪ With someone else ♪

00:17.935 --> 00:21.730
♪ Together we will soar
Across the sky and beyond ♪

00:21.730 --> 00:23.232
♪ So turn up your voice ♪

00:23.941 --> 00:25.692
♪ Stand up and sing along ♪

00:25.692 --> 00:26.902
♪ All different voices ♪

00:26.902 --> 00:27.819
♪ Everybody now! ♪

00:27.819 --> 00:29.363
♪ Our melodies ringing ♪

00:29.363 --> 00:31.073
♪ We're livin' in harmony ♪

00:31.073 --> 00:33.242
♪ Yeah, we're livin' in harmony ♪

00:33.242 --> 00:37.037
♪ Our song is much stronger
With every troll singing ♪

00:37.037 --> 00:39.373
♪ We're livin' in harmony ♪♪

00:43.377 --> 00:46.004
[ Poppy humming ]

00:46.004 --> 00:48.298
‐ Good morning.
‐ Good morning, Queen Poppy!

00:49.174 --> 00:51.551
‐ Okay! Top spin coming at you.

00:52.970 --> 00:54.471
‐ Alright, Tiny!

00:54.471 --> 00:57.224
Way to serve that ball... to...

00:59.643 --> 01:00.560
nobody?

01:00.811 --> 01:03.939
Um, are you looking for someone
to play with?

01:03.939 --> 01:07.067
‐ What do you mean, Daddy's friend
Aunt Poppy? I've got someone.

01:07.067 --> 01:08.777
He's the P in my posse,

01:08.777 --> 01:11.071
he turns on my entourage,

01:11.071 --> 01:14.658
he's Shiny Diamond!

01:17.703 --> 01:20.122
‐ But, Tiny, there's nobody‐‐

01:20.330 --> 01:23.041
‐ Now give me some
of homie handshake love, Shiny D!

01:24.334 --> 01:25.377
Okay, yeah.

01:26.503 --> 01:27.379
Up top. Yeah.

01:27.671 --> 01:29.381
Okay, let's go! Already.

01:29.840 --> 01:31.341
‐ Poppy?
‐ Oh, hey, Guy.

01:31.717 --> 01:32.968
‐ Just a little hairs up,

01:33.302 --> 01:36.054
Shiny Diamond is
Tiny's new imaginary friend.

01:36.054 --> 01:40.017
‐ Oh, an imaginary friend!

01:40.017 --> 01:43.270
‐ Yes, but to Tiny, he's very real.

01:43.437 --> 01:45.272
He means the world to my little guy.

01:45.439 --> 01:46.940
‐ Yeah, no, of course.

01:47.190 --> 01:49.818
When I was a kid,
I had an imaginary friend too,

01:50.652 --> 01:51.653
Brunhilda.

01:52.571 --> 01:55.907
She always made me feel so safe,
'cause no matter where I went,

01:56.241 --> 02:00.579
even when I was all alone,
I always had a good friend close by.

02:01.455 --> 02:04.666
But I haven't not seen her
in a long time.

02:06.793 --> 02:10.922
Don't worry, Guy, I would never do
anything to spoil this for Tiny.

02:11.465 --> 02:13.884
‐ Yeah! Uh‐huh. Up top, Shiny!

02:14.051 --> 02:15.510
Okay, let's go. Yeah!

02:15.844 --> 02:17.054
Here we go, up top.

02:17.888 --> 02:21.016
Dismount and...
handshake over, people.

02:21.892 --> 02:24.353
‐ Woo! So impressive!

02:24.770 --> 02:27.356
Well, Shiny,
it was a pleasure meeting you.

02:27.564 --> 02:28.982
Oh, strong grip.

02:29.524 --> 02:34.529
Okay, I'm up to hang out with Val,
have a super fun day, you two!

02:34.780 --> 02:37.783
‐ Wait, you're just going to leave,
Aunt Poppy?

02:38.867 --> 02:40.285
‐ Uh, what do you mean?

02:40.452 --> 02:43.622
Well, usually, when you meet
somebody new,

02:43.622 --> 02:45.624
you drop everything
to get to know them.

02:45.624 --> 02:48.377
‐ Huh, I guess I do, don't I?

02:48.669 --> 02:51.963
‐ Yeah, so? Why wouldn't you do it
for Shiny Diamond?

02:52.297 --> 02:55.467
‐ Why? Um...

02:56.426 --> 02:58.095
No reason at all!

02:58.095 --> 03:02.224
I would love to spend
some get‐to‐know‐you time with Shiny!

03:02.599 --> 03:04.184
‐ Well, alright, Aunty P!

03:04.351 --> 03:07.312
Then let's level up this party,
Shiny Diamond style!

03:07.562 --> 03:09.690
Yeah, yeah, yeah! Yeah!

03:13.110 --> 03:16.113
♪ You'll be best friends forever ♪

03:16.488 --> 03:18.448
♪ And ever to the end ♪

03:18.448 --> 03:21.326
♪ Every day that we're together ♪

03:21.827 --> 03:23.662
♪ Is another day well spent ♪

03:23.662 --> 03:25.705
♪ Yeah, we'll be best friends forever ♪

03:25.705 --> 03:28.250
♪ And never, never better
Than when we're together ♪

03:28.250 --> 03:30.877
♪ Whether we're playing hide and seek
Or maybe freeze ♪

03:30.877 --> 03:31.795
♪ Tag is never bad ♪

03:31.795 --> 03:35.006
♪ It's like we have ESP
I get you, you get me ♪

03:35.006 --> 03:38.009
♪ And it's hard to imagine
There's anyone else out there ♪

03:38.009 --> 03:41.012
♪ Who sparkles like us
And make just as good a pair ♪

03:41.012 --> 03:43.014
♪ The way we do is me and me you ♪

03:43.014 --> 03:46.643
♪ Through and through, hand in hand
We'll be best friends to the very end! ♪

03:46.643 --> 03:48.353
♪ You'll be best friends forever ♪

03:48.353 --> 03:50.522
♪ And ever to the end ♪

03:50.522 --> 03:53.316
♪ Every day that we're together ♪

03:53.900 --> 03:56.069
♪ Is another day well spent ♪♪

03:56.069 --> 03:57.279
‐ Take it away, Shiny.

04:00.407 --> 04:02.492
Oh, mic drop!

04:02.909 --> 04:05.245
Tiny and Shiny out!

04:06.455 --> 04:10.625
Yeah, way to jump rope, Shiny D! Woo!

04:12.669 --> 04:15.130
‐ Popsqueak!
I thought we we're going to hang.

04:16.298 --> 04:19.718
Uh, well, this looks...

04:20.510 --> 04:23.764
I don't know, bizarre? Painful?
Pick your adjective.

04:23.972 --> 04:25.640
‐ Sorry, Val, it's just...

04:26.057 --> 04:29.728
Tiny wanted me to spend time
with his imaginary friend Shiny‐‐

04:32.022 --> 04:36.359
And I don't want knowing
Shiny isn't real, so I went along with it?

04:37.444 --> 04:40.697
‐ Oh. Well, I know
this isn't really like me,

04:40.697 --> 04:43.450
but I actually think that's very sweet.

04:43.450 --> 04:45.035
‐ Really?
‐ No!

04:45.494 --> 04:46.328
‐ Oh.

04:46.328 --> 04:49.748
‐ Poppy, what's your plan here?
You're just going to keep letting him

04:49.748 --> 04:52.417
yank on your hair forever
to protect him from the truth?

04:52.417 --> 04:56.546
‐ Not forever, I'm sure Shiny
will get bored of jumping hair eventually.

04:57.339 --> 04:58.965
‐ Shiny's bored of jumping hair.

04:59.299 --> 05:01.092
‐ Oh, really?

05:01.343 --> 05:02.344
See?

05:02.344 --> 05:04.679
‐ Now he wants you to teach him
how to ride a bike.

05:04.805 --> 05:06.139
‐ Aw!

05:07.182 --> 05:08.183
Sorry, what now?

05:09.267 --> 05:15.273
So you want me to teach Shiny
how to ride a bike all on his own?

05:15.649 --> 05:16.650
‐ Why, Popsqueak?

05:17.192 --> 05:20.278
Is there some reason
you can't teach Shiny?

05:20.529 --> 05:22.697
‐ Yeah, Aunt Poppy, is there a reason?

05:22.989 --> 05:24.616
‐ No, no, no!

05:24.950 --> 05:25.784
Reason?

05:26.201 --> 05:28.495
So... I'll just...

05:30.997 --> 05:33.792
‐ Okay, he's ready, Aunt Poppy, let go!

05:34.042 --> 05:36.753
‐ You sure, Tiny? Maybe we should‐‐!

05:36.753 --> 05:39.172
‐ He'll never learn if you don't let go!

05:39.464 --> 05:41.174
He's ready, Aunt Poppy!

05:44.177 --> 05:45.178
[ Poppy gasps ]

05:46.847 --> 05:47.931
[ Tiny Diamond gasps ]

05:52.310 --> 05:55.355
Oh! He wasn't ready!

05:55.647 --> 05:58.066
He wasn't ready, Aunt Poppy!

05:58.191 --> 05:59.484
POPPY:
No, no, no, no!

06:00.277 --> 06:03.738
‐ Shiny? Shiny, please,
tell your boy you're not hurt.

06:04.531 --> 06:06.366
Uh‐huh, uh‐huh, yeah.

06:07.242 --> 06:08.702
Okay. Uh‐huh.

06:08.869 --> 06:09.953
No, just speak up.

06:10.579 --> 06:11.580
Yeah, okay, uh‐huh.

06:12.122 --> 06:15.250
Well, he's got no cuts or broken bones.

06:15.625 --> 06:16.751
‐ Oh, that's good.

06:17.335 --> 06:20.338
‐ But he says the emotional trauma
runs real deep.

06:21.590 --> 06:25.176
Dang, dang,
it should've been me.

06:28.388 --> 06:30.849
‐ Oh, Tiny, don't be sad.

06:30.849 --> 06:34.728
Believe me, Shiny isn't upset, not really.

06:35.395 --> 06:38.523
‐ Wait, he isn't?
But he just said he is.

06:39.190 --> 06:43.612
‐ Oh. Uh, well, yeah, true.

06:43.612 --> 06:45.989
‐ Well, then why'd you say
he's not really upset?

06:46.531 --> 06:47.741
What do you mean by that?

06:47.949 --> 06:51.911
‐ Uh... Well, I... All I meant was...
um...

06:55.165 --> 06:57.626
Wait, I know what will cheer Shiny up!

07:01.129 --> 07:02.881
His very own...

07:03.256 --> 07:04.883
cuddle puppy!

07:07.135 --> 07:07.969
‐ What?

07:08.345 --> 07:09.179
Oh.

07:10.013 --> 07:11.264
Oh, he's so cute!

07:12.390 --> 07:13.683
He's licking my face!

07:14.517 --> 07:15.602
Here, Shiny.

07:19.731 --> 07:21.983
‐ Who's a good boy? Who's a good boy?

07:23.401 --> 07:25.362
Yeah! Throw the stick, Shiny!

07:26.946 --> 07:28.114
Go get it, Glitter Dog!

07:32.410 --> 07:35.080
‐ Oh, please, Val, stop sulking!

07:35.288 --> 07:40.669
Shiny's happy again, and all I did
was feed into Tiny's fantasy a little.

07:40.919 --> 07:42.253
What's the harm in that?

07:42.253 --> 07:43.838
TINY DIAMOND: <i>Aunt Poppy</i>!
‐ Ah!

07:43.838 --> 07:46.049
‐ Glitter Dog is gone!
‐ What?

07:46.049 --> 07:48.051
‐ He just ran off into the woods!

07:48.051 --> 07:50.929
Shiny's worried sick,
we got to go find him!

07:51.262 --> 07:52.263
Come on, everybody!

07:53.640 --> 07:55.266
‐ Um, you were saying?

07:57.852 --> 08:00.730
‐ Glitter Dog? Glitter Dog!

08:01.022 --> 08:03.983
‐ Wait, Tiny, it's okay,
Glitter Dog is, um...

08:04.984 --> 08:05.819
right here!

08:06.528 --> 08:08.738
‐ No, he's not,
that's some other dog.

08:09.698 --> 08:10.907
‐ Uh, huh‐huh.

08:12.617 --> 08:14.411
Uh... huh?

08:15.078 --> 08:16.871
‐ Well, now you're holding nothing!

08:16.871 --> 08:18.039
Is this a game to you?

08:19.165 --> 08:20.709
Wait, you hear that barking?

08:21.167 --> 08:22.001
‐ Barking?

08:25.839 --> 08:26.840
‐ There he is!

08:27.173 --> 08:28.174
‐ Oh, good.

08:30.135 --> 08:31.761
‐ Oh, wow.

08:31.761 --> 08:36.224
‐ He's stuck in the middle of that bridge!
You got to rescue him, Aunt Poppy!

08:43.940 --> 08:44.774
‐Ah!
‐Ah!

08:45.191 --> 08:49.571
Okay, Poppy, this whole situation
has gotten officially very uncool.

08:49.904 --> 08:51.239
You cannot go out there.

08:51.698 --> 08:54.325
‐ Yeah, yeah, Val,
I think you're right.

08:54.826 --> 08:56.119
Tiny... I...

08:56.119 --> 08:57.078
[ Poppy gasps ]

08:57.078 --> 09:00.081
‐ Please, Aunt Poppy,
save Glitter Dog...

09:00.540 --> 09:01.583
for Shiny.

09:05.420 --> 09:08.048
‐ Never mind, I'm going out there!

09:08.590 --> 09:09.466
‐ Yeah!

09:09.466 --> 09:10.550
‐ Seriously?

09:11.342 --> 09:13.011
‐ Yes, Val, seriously.

09:16.181 --> 09:18.558
‐ Poppy, stop! Come back!

09:18.850 --> 09:21.936
‐ Keep going, Aunt Poppy,
I believe in you!

09:22.145 --> 09:25.315
‐ No, don't! This is way out of hand!

09:25.315 --> 09:29.694
‐ You're setting a heroic example
for my impressionable young mind!

09:29.986 --> 09:30.904
‐ Ugh.

09:31.905 --> 09:35.241
‐ It's okay, Val! It seems pretty sturdy!

09:35.366 --> 09:38.203
Looks like some French braid action
on these joists,

09:38.203 --> 09:40.246
so I think it's pretty safe‐‐ Ah!

09:44.709 --> 09:46.586
Okay, other than that,

09:46.711 --> 09:48.463
I think it's pretty safe. Ah!

09:49.214 --> 09:52.509
Uh... other than that...

09:54.886 --> 09:55.804
Hey!

09:56.596 --> 09:57.931
Okay, forget this.

09:58.848 --> 10:02.519
Clearly, I've taken things way too far,
I'm coming back.

10:02.685 --> 10:04.062
Ah! Ah!

10:04.062 --> 10:05.063
‐ Ah!
‐ Ah!

10:05.563 --> 10:07.273
Ah!

10:08.566 --> 10:11.277
POPPY:
No!

10:22.122 --> 10:23.039
Thank you, Val.

10:24.040 --> 10:25.667
‐ Can you just tell him already?

10:29.295 --> 10:33.258
‐ Tiny, I've been trying to avoid this
all day, but...

10:33.883 --> 10:35.844
there's something I've got to tell you.

10:37.053 --> 10:40.473
‐ No, Aunt Poppy, there's something
I've got to tell <i>you</i>.

10:43.059 --> 10:45.103
Shiny Diamond isn't real.

10:47.105 --> 10:47.981
‐ What?

10:48.189 --> 10:50.483
You knew? When did you...?

10:50.942 --> 10:52.986
‐ About 15 minutes after I imagined him,

10:53.194 --> 10:56.030
but then you clearly seemed
to think he was real,

10:56.281 --> 10:59.159
and I didn't want to spoil it for you,
so...

11:00.118 --> 11:03.121
‐ But I went out on the bridge.

11:07.250 --> 11:10.962
‐ Yeah, in hindsight,
Tiny Diamond took that part way too far.

11:11.129 --> 11:13.798
But hey, I'm just a kid,
what's your excuse?

11:14.007 --> 11:16.092
‐ But‐‐ But, I almost‐‐

11:16.092 --> 11:18.011
‐ Okay, glad we got that all worked out.

11:18.303 --> 11:19.596
It's been real.

11:19.804 --> 11:22.682
Bless up! Tiny out.

11:23.725 --> 11:24.642
‐ Uh...

11:25.059 --> 11:27.770
‐ Wow. Am I glad that's over with,

11:28.104 --> 11:32.025
because now I can finally introduce you
to Rockarella,

11:32.025 --> 11:36.404
and boy, oh, boy, do we have
some fun things planned for you!

11:50.418 --> 11:52.170
[ alien speaking unintelligibly ]

11:52.420 --> 11:55.882
‐ Captain, the alien sent a message,
and it's as you suspected,

11:55.882 --> 11:57.926
they say they rock harder than we can!

12:01.763 --> 12:03.014
‐ What are we going to do?

12:04.015 --> 12:05.850
‐ I'll tell you what I'm going to do,

12:06.476 --> 12:09.395
I'm going to get out of the way
so you can talk to the captain.

12:11.314 --> 12:13.983
‐ Set photons to hardcore.

12:19.364 --> 12:20.406
Rock on.

12:21.616 --> 12:25.411
[ Val and Alien playing metal music ]

12:31.918 --> 12:35.922
[ Val making guitar sounds ]

12:35.922 --> 12:38.007
‐ Uh... is she okay?

12:38.341 --> 12:41.636
‐ Yep, Val's just been
in a Hard Rock sci‐fi fantasy

12:41.636 --> 12:43.930
ever since Lownote Jones'
big announcement.

12:44.305 --> 12:46.266
To help us explore Funk culture,

12:46.432 --> 12:50.645
he's going to let any Troll who wants
to fly the Vibe Town spaceship.

12:51.187 --> 12:53.064
‐ Wow!

12:53.481 --> 12:57.068
‐ All you have to do is take
his week‐long flying class first.

12:57.068 --> 12:59.153
‐ Wait, I got to take what now?

13:00.321 --> 13:01.698
‐ My name...

13:02.949 --> 13:04.367
is Mr...

13:05.910 --> 13:06.744
[ Val sighs ]

13:07.537 --> 13:08.997
‐ Lownote...

13:09.497 --> 13:10.665
‐ Ah...

13:11.457 --> 13:12.750
‐ Jones.

13:14.961 --> 13:16.296
‐ Ugh, finally.

13:16.963 --> 13:18.506
‐ Baby.

13:18.881 --> 13:20.049
‐ Oh...

13:21.384 --> 13:23.177
‐ Any questions before we begin?

13:23.553 --> 13:28.766
‐ Oh, oh! Mr. Lownote, sitting still
at a desk listening to lessons all day

13:29.142 --> 13:33.354
isn't exactly my jam,
any way I could skip it?

13:34.981 --> 13:37.984
‐ What a delightfully shortsighted
question, Val.

13:39.402 --> 13:42.363
You see, space piloting is very,
very difficult.

13:42.363 --> 13:44.574
And while I'll be with you
during your flight

13:44.574 --> 13:46.409
to make sure you're 100% safe,

13:46.659 --> 13:49.912
nobody can fly Vibe Town
without taking the class

13:49.912 --> 13:51.873
and passing the final exam.

13:52.290 --> 13:55.334
‐ Oh, Mr. Lownote, same exact question,

13:55.334 --> 13:57.545
just rephrased
in a slightly different way,

13:57.920 --> 14:01.132
can I, please, just fly Vibe Town
right now?

14:01.132 --> 14:02.258
[ bell dings ]

14:03.009 --> 14:05.887
‐ Well, sure you can.

14:06.304 --> 14:07.263
‐ Yes!

14:07.263 --> 14:08.681
[ Val making guitar sounds ]

14:08.681 --> 14:10.475
‐ In textbook form!

14:10.475 --> 14:11.392
‐ Huh?

14:11.392 --> 14:13.019
‐ Oh!
‐ Oh!

14:13.227 --> 14:15.104
‐ Welcome to the exciting world

14:15.104 --> 14:18.274
of reading about the exciting world
of flying.

14:18.649 --> 14:20.902
[ students talking indistinctly ]

14:23.946 --> 14:27.742
‐ Woo, this spaceship class
is a brain‐wrinkler, yo.

14:27.867 --> 14:31.412
Cylindrical Interstellar Warp Core
technology ain't as easy

14:31.412 --> 14:33.498
as my Mama led me to believe.

14:34.290 --> 14:37.293
‐ Hey, Val, we're forming
a study‐buddy group,

14:37.293 --> 14:40.338
want to be a study buddy and study, buddy?

14:40.588 --> 14:45.176
‐ Hmm, I would, but I worry
it'll conflict with my preexistent plans

14:45.176 --> 14:48.930
to not study and goof off, so...

14:49.764 --> 14:50.973
‐ Not study?

14:51.140 --> 14:56.479
Uh, Val, you do realize that you don't get
to fly if you don't pass the test, right?

14:56.687 --> 15:01.692
‐ Oh, I'll pass, using a little thing
I call the Val method.

15:03.820 --> 15:06.197
What's the Val method? Glad you asked.

15:06.531 --> 15:08.157
‐ We didn't!
‐ The Val method

15:08.157 --> 15:12.203
is a set of guidelines that help me
crush a test while making the bare

15:12.203 --> 15:13.371
minimum of effort.

15:14.288 --> 15:17.750
Guideline number one,
every teacher has a tell.

15:18.417 --> 15:19.794
Take Lownote, for example.

15:19.794 --> 15:22.755
Whenever he's about to say something
that'll be on the test,

15:22.755 --> 15:24.966
he clears his throat
and raises an eyebrow.

15:25.550 --> 15:26.384
‐ Now...

15:26.384 --> 15:27.677
[ Lownote clears throat ]

15:27.802 --> 15:30.513
This button activates
the ship's vertical thrust...

15:30.680 --> 15:32.473
<i>‐ Which means I got to pay attention.</i>

15:32.765 --> 15:34.851
<i>But when the brow goes down</i>...

15:34.851 --> 15:38.521
‐ And this button
activates the ship's cup holders.

15:38.729 --> 15:41.357
<i>‐ That's my cue to think</i>
<i>about nothing but Val stuff</i>.

15:45.153 --> 15:46.112
[ Lownote coughs ]

15:46.737 --> 15:49.615
‐ When driving a spaceship,
keep your hands at 10...

15:49.866 --> 15:51.117
and 2,000,

15:51.659 --> 15:53.995
depending on which galaxy's clock
you go by.

15:54.370 --> 15:56.247
Now, this button activates...

15:58.708 --> 15:59.959
[ Lownote clears throat ]

16:00.042 --> 16:03.337
Interstellar objects in the mirror
are closer than they appear.

16:08.050 --> 16:10.511
♪ Val method! ♪♪

16:11.137 --> 16:12.763
Guideline number two,

16:12.972 --> 16:15.391
there's always a risk
the teacher will call on you

16:15.391 --> 16:16.767
when you're not listening.

16:16.976 --> 16:18.019
‐ Val Thundershock?

16:19.854 --> 16:22.440
When is the right time
to pull the red lever?

16:22.815 --> 16:24.025
‐ Uh...

16:24.025 --> 16:27.403
<i>So just stay calm and restate</i>
<i>the question as an answer.</i>

16:28.279 --> 16:32.241
Well, frankly, any time is the right time
to pull the red lever,

16:32.241 --> 16:35.620
provided it's not the wrong time
to pull the red lever.

16:39.916 --> 16:40.833
‐ Very true.

16:40.833 --> 16:42.627
Did everyone hear what Val just said?

16:42.793 --> 16:44.003
[ students murmuring ]

16:44.003 --> 16:45.087
‐ Val method.

16:46.923 --> 16:49.383
<i>Guideline</i> numero <i>three‐o,</i>

16:49.675 --> 16:52.929
<i>if you really need some R&R</i>
<i>from the boring Q&A,</i>

16:53.221 --> 16:55.973
<i>get the teacher talking</i>
<i>about stuff they really like</i>.

